### 分析氣溫數據
%sh wget https://github.com/ywchiu/sparkcht/raw/master/Data/1800.csv

%pyspark 
lines = sc.textFile("/tmp/1800.csv")
print lines.take(2)


def parseLine(line):
    fields = line.split(',')
    stationID = fields[0]
    entryType = fields[2]
    temperature = float(fields[3]) * 0.1 * (9.0 / 5.0) + 32.0
    return (stationID, entryType, temperature)
    
parsedLines = lines.map(parseLine)
print parsedLines.take(2)

minTemps = parsedLines.filter(lambda e: 'TMIN' in e[1])
print minTemps.take(2)


stationTemps = minTemps.map(lambda e: (e[0], e[2]) )
print stationTemps.take(2)

minTemps = stationTemps.reduceByKey(lambda x, y: min(x,y))
print minTemps.take(2)

results = minTemps.collect()

for result in results:
    print result[0], result[1]

%pyspark 
input = sc.textFile("/tmp/cnn.txt")
words = input.map(lambda e: e.upper())
segment = words.flatMap(lambda e: e.split())
#print segment.take(100)

wordCounts = segment.countByValue()

from operator import itemgetter
swd = sorted (wordCounts.items(), key =itemgetter(1), reverse=True)

for key, value in swd:
    print "%s %i" % (key, value)
